OL,3,CMillions of customers facing parcel
OL,4,Cdelivery problems - here's how to
OL,5,Csolve them
OL,7,FUnder consumer law, retailers which
OL,8,Fsell products are responsible for
OL,9,Fmaking sure items are delivered to you.
OL,11,FIf your parcel doesn't turn up, or the
OL,12,Fitem is damaged, you must contact
OL,13,Fwhoever you've bought it from, as they
OL,14,Flegally have to resolve the issue.
OL,16,FBut you should complain to the
OL,17,Fdelivery company directly if you've
OL,18,Fhad a problem with how the parcel has
OL,19,Fbeen delivered, such as the conduct of
OL,20,Fthe delivery driver.
